ZH: 我去看恐怖电影时，我的手开始发颤。
EN: My hands started trembling when I went to watch a horror movie.

ZH: 我听到那个消息时，我的声音变得发颤了。
EN: My voice started trembling when I heard that news.

ZH: 他紧张得整个身体都开始发颤。
EN: His whole body started trembling due to nervousness.

ZH: 那只小狗受到吓到，全身发颤地躲在角落里。
EN: The little dog got scared and hid in the corner, trembling all over.

ZH: 当我上台发表演讲时，我感到自己的腿开始发颤了。
EN: When I went on stage to give a speech, I felt my legs starting to tremble.

ZH: 当他们宣布我是幸运抽奖者时，我激动得全身都发颤。
EN: When they announced that I was the lucky winner, I was so excited that my whole body trembled.

ZH: 冬天的寒冷气候让我发颤。
EN: The cold weather in winter makes me tremble.

ZH: 看到那么多蜘蛛，他的身体开始不自觉地发颤。
EN: Seeing so many spiders, his body started trembling involuntarily.

ZH: 当我看到她受到欺负时，我的身体发颤地想要保护她。
EN: When I saw her being bullied, my body trembled as I wanted to protect her.

ZH: 在恶劣的天气中，我不禁开始发颤。
EN: In harsh weather conditions, I started trembling involuntarily.

ZH: 当他紧紧握住我的手时，我觉得自己的心发颤了一下。
EN: When he tightly held my hand, I felt a tremor in my heart.

ZH: 看到我的父母亲吵架，我感到自己的声音开始发颤。
EN: Seeing my parents argue, I felt my voice start trembling.

ZH: 看到这么多人聚集在一起，他感到自己的喉咙发颤。
EN: Being surrounded by so many people, he felt a tremor in his throat.

ZH: 在紧急情况下，我的双腿开始不受控制地发颤。
EN: In an emergency, my legs started trembling uncontrollably.

ZH: 当我接到这个好消息时，我感到自己的全身都在发颤。
EN: When I received this good news, I felt my whole body trembling.

ZH: 当我遇到危险时，我的身体本能地开始发颤。
EN: When I encountered danger, my body instinctively started trembling.

ZH: 当我走近边缘时，我的脚踝开始发颤。
EN: When I approached the edge, my ankles started trembling.

ZH: 看到她这样伤心，我的眼睛开始发颤了。
EN: Seeing her so sad, my eyes started trembling.

